<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-05-12</DATELINE><TITLE>Novel Lyssavirus in Bat, Spain</TITLE><BODY>A new tentative lyssavirus, Lleida bat lyssavirus, was found in a bent-winged bat (Miniopterus schreibersii) in Spain. It does not belong to phylogroups I or II, and it seems to be more closely related to the West Causasian bat virus, and especially to the Ikoma lyssavirus.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>